gh issue create --repo "$REPO" \
  --title 'Puzzle generation + /puzzle and /guess (single-token)' \
  --milestone 'M1: MVP' \
  --label 'area:server' \
  --body-file - <<'WORDGUESS_ISSUE_BODY'
Build the single-token puzzle loop and expose it over HTTP. Generation: take a random slice of the corpus as the prompt, compute the next-char distribution, set correct = argmax char and distractors = ranks 2..K, shuffle the choices, and cache the answer server-side keyed by puzzle_id. Endpoints: POST /puzzle -> {puzzle_id, prompt, choices[]} and POST /guess -> {puzzle_id, choice_idx} -> {correct_idx, probs[], your_prob, score?}.

## Acceptance criteria

- [ ] POST /puzzle returns a puzzle_id, a prompt, and shuffled choices; the correct index is NOT inferable from the response.
- [ ] The correct answer and per-choice probabilities are stored in a short-lived in-memory cache keyed by puzzle_id.
- [ ] POST /guess returns correct_idx, the probability spread, and the probability the player's choice carried.
- [ ] Guessing an unknown or expired puzzle_id returns a clean 404-style error.
- [ ] A basic score is derived from the probability mass of the guess.

## Out of scope

- No next-word rollout (M2 replaces the single-token candidates).
- No persistent storage — in-memory cache only.
- No multi-corpus routing (M3).
WORDGUESS_ISSUE_BODY

