gh issue create --repo "$REPO" \
  --title 'Next-word greedy rollout in the inference layer' \
  --milestone 'M2: Next-word puzzles' \
  --label 'area:model' --label 'area:server' \
  --body-file - <<'WORDGUESS_ISSUE_BODY'
Add the greedy rollout primitive. Given a prompt, take the top-K first next-chars, and for each roll forward greedily char-by-char until a word boundary (whitespace/punctuation), multiplying probabilities along the way. Return one candidate word per branch with its cumulative probability.

## Acceptance criteria

- [ ] `rollout_words(prompt, k) -> list[(word, cumulative_prob)]` returns K candidate words.
- [ ] Each rollout stops at the first word boundary after the branch point.
- [ ] Cumulative probability is the product of per-step probabilities along the greedy path.
- [ ] Candidates are de-duplicated if two branches produce the same word (keep the higher probability).
- [ ] A script prints the candidate words and probabilities for a sample prompt.

## Out of scope

- No beam search — greedy per-branch only.
- No endpoint changes in this issue (next issue wires it in).
- No scoring changes yet.
